      <section id="breakeven">
        <h2>The break-even calculation: finding your magic number</h2>
        <p>
          Instead of guessing, here's how to find your personal break-even point:
        </p>

        <h3>Step 1: Calculate tax under new regime</h3>
        <p>
          Take your gross salary, subtract ₹75,000 standard deduction. Apply new regime
          slabs. This is your new regime tax.
        </p>

        <h3>Step 2: Calculate tax under old regime with your actual deductions</h3>
        <p>
          Take gross salary, subtract ₹50,000 standard deduction, then subtract all your
          80C, 80D, HRA, home loan, NPS deductions. Apply old regime slabs.
        </p>

        <h3>Step 3: Compare</h3>
        <p>
          Whichever regime produces the lower tax number is your answer.
        </p>

